Package org.neo4j.internal.id.indexed

Class IdRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.id.indexed.IdRange
  • class IdRange
extends Object
    Value in a GB+Tree for indexing id states. Accompanies that with a generation, i.e. which generation this value were written in. ID states are kept in three bit-sets, each consisting of one or more longs. The three bit-sets are:
    • Commit bits, i.e. 0=used, 1=unused
    • Reuse bits, i.e. 0=not reusable, 1=free
    • Reserved bits, i.e. 0=not reserved, 1=reserved
    Each IdRange is associated with an IdRangeKey which specifies the range, e.g. an ID range of 3 in a layout where ids-per-entry is 128 holds IDs between 384-511.
